    {
      "id": "da6721732003e8a81082c6e4abe41690f339f18a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-06-19 08:23:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWhat are the purposes of the changes in acceptance-small.sh?\n\nMy http://review.whamcloud.com/2907 will actually remove \"--mkfsoptions\" from local.sh.  Users should be and are able to format Lustre targets without specifying \"--mkfsoptions\".  I believe that should be the typical case we should test by default.  There could be a conf-sanity test verifying \"--mkfsoptions\" works.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "25cf80cf0a4bcfeaa451e7fc02afd85f7e0d188b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-06-19 22:50:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Abandoned\n\nThe main intent of this patch was to restore the \"errors=remount-ro\" option for mkfs.lustre to quiet test warnings, but this is covered by Li Wei's more important patch.\n\nThe change to acceptance-small.sh was unintentional, and was intended for a separate patch.  This is also obsoleted by another patch I'm working on (http://review.whamcloud.com/3132) which replaces the guts of acc-sm.sh with a call to auster, so that we don't need to maintain duplicate code to run the tests.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    }
  ],
